# cs373-idb-mythos
The Mythos API allows you to get access to the **Mythos Database API** (MDB), a database for mythological **figures**, **cultures**, and **stories**.

# Group Figures
Figure related resources of the **MDB API**

## Figures [/figures]
### List all figures [GET]
+ Response 200 (application/json)
        
        [{
            "id": 1,
            "title":"Atlas",
            "kind":"Titan",
            "biography":"Long text description here."
        }, {
            "id": 2,
            "title":"Athena",
            "kind":"Olympian",
            "biography":"Long text description here."
        }, {
            "id": 3,
            "title":"Loki",
            "kind":"God",
            "biography":"Long text description here."
        }]

### Create a figure [POST]
+ Request (application/json)

        {
            "title":"Loki",
            "kind":"God",
            "biography":"Long text description here."
            "images":[Media(link="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/40/Processed_SAM_loki.jpg"),
                      Media(link="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/ac/Loki_taunts_Bragi.jpg"),
                      Media(link="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/cb/Louis_Huard_-_The_Punishment_of_Loki.jpg")],
            "videos":[Media(link="http://www.youtube.com/embed/o43-oAL2ogY")],
            "related_figures":[],
            "related_stories":[],
            "related_cultures":[Culture(id=3, name="Nordic")],
            "external_links":[Media(name="Wikipedia: Loki", link="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Loki"),
                              Media(name="Pantheon.Org", link="http://www.pantheon.org/articles/l/loki.html")]
        }

+ Response 201 (application/json)

        {
            "id": 3
        }

## Figure [/figures/{id}]
A single figure object with all its details

+ Parameters
    + id (required, number, `1`) ... Numeric `id` of the Figure to perform action with. Has example value.

### Retrieve a figure [GET]
+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "id": 3,
            "title":"Loki",
            "kind":"God",
            "biography":"Long text description here.",
            "images":[Media(link="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/40/Processed_SAM_loki.jpg"),
                      Media(link="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/ac/Loki_taunts_Bragi.jpg"),
                      Media(link="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/cb/Louis_Huard_-_The_Punishment_of_Loki.jpg")],
            "videos":[Media(link="http://www.youtube.com/embed/o43-oAL2ogY")],
            "related_figures":[],
            "related_stories":[],
            "related_cultures":[Culture(id=3, name="Nordic")],
            "external_links":[Media(name="Wikipedia: Loki", link="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Loki"),
                              Media(name="Pantheon.Org", link="http://www.pantheon.org/articles/l/loki.html")]
        }

### Remove a figure [DELETE]
+ Response 204

